    <text id="A3054T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Plunkett writes to the husband of his brother's childhood friend, asking him to
                    send tobacco, as Plunkett has run out of money.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Rev Mr. Miller<lb/>Little York<lb/>Penn</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-07-07">July the 7 1864</date>
                        <name type="place">Fort <orig reg="Delaware">Deleware</orig></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Reverend">rev</abbr> Mr Miller Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I <orig reg="write">wright</orig> you a line seeking a <orig reg="favor"
                    >favour</orig> from I am a prisoner at this place entirely <orig reg="destitute"
                        >distute</orig> of funds &amp; have no means of procuring tobacco I have
                    written to several acquaintances but none have responded yet you can imagine
                    that a small amount of tobacco <orig reg="would">wold</orig> be very thankfully
                        <orig reg="received">recivd</orig> by myself &amp; Comrad James Steel
                    who is also a Prisoner I should not of known you whereabout but for my Brother
                    was fortunate to meet with you last <orig reg="summer">sumer</orig>. I suppose
                    you do not <orig reg="know">no</orig> my name <orig reg="your">yore</orig> lady
                        <orig reg="remembers">remebers</orig> my name I lived in Middlebrook with
                    her Brothers if you can <orig reg="consistently">consistantly</orig> send us a
                    small <orig reg="package">pacage</orig> of tobacco we will be very thankful
                    Direct to James Steel &amp; John H. Plunkett <abbr expan="Company"
                    >comp</abbr> E 5 <orig reg="Regiment">Regment</orig> of Virginia infantry</p>
                <p>care Capt Ahl <unclear>George W.</unclear> the <orig reg="Authorities"
                    >Athorities</orig> here admit all contributions <unclear>9</unclear> division</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed/>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
